𐌸 ⋍ Θ Theta

𐌳 and 𐌸 appear to be very similar:
𐌲𐍉𐌳𐍃 guds gōds gut, good, gütig
𐌲𐍉𐌸𐍃 guƌs gōƌs gut, good, gütig

No apparent connections to feather pth psi ψ Ψ feather ƒt φ Φ in its gothic usage! Except (weakly)
𓅓𓏱𓏏 Mwrt > mwt מות māweṯ, Arabic: موت mawt
𓅓𓏱𓏏 Mwrt > 𐌼𐌰𐌿𐍂𐌸𐍂𐌾𐌰𐌽 mørƌrɕen morden, murder,kill (𐌸 weṯ/töt)

Until one sees the Nomen sacrum reading of 𐌲𐌿𐌸 God = Jupiter

Sometimes the vulgar reading can be very different to the (imaginary) archaic reading:
𐌸𐍃 ds ⋍ dg ⋍ gth
𐍃𐍅𐌹𐌽𐌸𐍃 strength geschwind?
𐍃𐌰𐌿𐌸𐍃 Sendung
𐍃𐌰𐌿𐌸𐍃 sacrifice
𐍅𐌹𐌻𐌸𐌴𐌹𐍃 wild/wolfish
𐌿𐌽𐌻𐌴𐌸𐍃 unlǣd:ohnLand poor

These are probably just 5 false artefacts.
